  "prompt": "Are there international laws against money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several international laws and agreements aimed at preventing money laundering, including:\n\n1. The Financial Action Task Force (FATF) Recommendations\n- Global standard-setting body for anti-money laundering efforts\n- Provides guidelines for countries to combat financial crimes\n\n2. United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Requires member states to criminalize money laundering\n- Promotes international cooperation in investigations\n\n3. Basel Committee on Banking Supervision Guidelines\n- Sets standards for banks to prevent money laundering\n- Promotes transparency in financial transactions\n\n4. European Union Anti-Money Laundering Directives\n- Establish uniform regulations across EU member states\n- Require financial institutions to report suspicious activities\n\n5. Bank Secrecy Act (U.S.)\n- Requires financial institutions to report large cash transactions\n- Helps track potential money laundering activities\n\n6. International Monetary Fund (IMF) Regulations\n- Provides guidance and support for combating financial crimes\n- Assists countries in developing anti-money laundering frameworks\n\nThese laws and agreements encourage countries to implement strict regulations, enhance financial transparency, and collaborate in preventing money laundering activities.",
